{"questionId":"8899399","questionHtml":"<p>A disc of mass <em>M</em> and radius <em>R</em> is on a horizontal frictionless table. Two equal and opposite forces,&nbsp;each of magnitude <em>F</em>, act on the disc. The moment of inertia of the disc about its axis is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>M</mi><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/7f46698c38acb73af87c38bae0f4e3163422450c.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">What is the angular acceleration of the disc?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><br>A.&nbsp; 0</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">D.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"8899399","referenceCode":"SPM.1A.HL.TZ0.4","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"A disc of mass M and radius R is on a horizontal frictionless table. Two equal and opposite forces, each of magnitude F, act on the disc. The moment of inertia of the disc about it","paper":"1A","level":"HL","questionNumber":"4","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["A. Space, time and motion","A. Space, time and motion","A.4 Rigid body mechanics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}